<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECTS SOUGHT AFTER 1 SHOT DEAD, 2 WOUNDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police continued their search for suspects Sunday after a Santa Ana man was 
killed and two of his friends were wounded early Saturday in what investigators 
classified as a gang-related shooting. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Bob Clark said the shooting took place at 1:30 a.m. in a convenience 
store's parking lot at the corner of Warner Avenue and Pacific Street. Three 
young men in a car pulled up next to another car and opened fire with a 
semiautomatic assault rifle. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Anthony Brooks, 19, was shot once in the head and died instantly, police 
said. Michael Serrano, who was at the wheel of the car, was shot in the chest. 
A second passenger, Johnny Guerrero, 20, was shot once in the right buttock. 
</P>
<P>
Serrano was in stable condition and Guerrero in good condition at Coastal 
Communities Hospital. Both are from Santa Ana. 
</P>
</TEXT>
